        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(update): continue after package doctor warnings",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Downgrade completed nonzero package post-install `openclaw doctor --fix` results to an advisory update step after the package install has already been verified.\n- Keep killed/timed-out doctor runs fatal so interrupted repairs do not continue into plugin convergence or gateway restart.\n- Surface advisory doctor stderr in both live progress and printed update summaries, then continue into the fresh post-core update process.\n- Fix the progress renderer typings for advisory doctor summary rows so the PR head passes the prod/test type gates.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `pnpm format:fix src/cli/update-cli/progress.ts src/cli/update-cli/update-command.ts src/cli/update-cli.test.ts`\n- `git diff --check`\n- `pnpm tsgo:prod`\n- `pnpm check:test-types`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/cli/update-cli.test.ts`\n- `.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode local` (clean: no accepted/actionable findings)\n- Real package update proof from a packed branch tarball with a Node preload hook that forces only the post-install `doctor` child to exit nonzero while `OPENCLAW_UPDATE_IN_PROGRESS=1` is set.\n\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: The `openclaw update` CLI package path continues past post-install doctor only for the dedicated exit code, a normally terminated child, and a valid typed deferred-configured-plugin-repair advisory, then runs mandatory post-core plugin convergence before restart. The non-converging generic `runGatewayUpdate` path keeps post-install doctor nonzero results blocking and does not participate in the advisory IPC contract.\n\nReal environment tested: The prior packed-package macOS update proof remains from ancestor head 377924d03129cc97b094c1d2681148e37487e5f0. Current head 408dcbeeee8949cf4125c495d010bf1f046fecda was tested in the isolated macOS PR worktree with Node 24.14.0 against upstream/main 4809ac70fa5aadded1a9e28e904eb35c266ebb1c.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch:\n\n```sh\nenv -u OPENCLAW_SERVICE_KIND -u OPENCLAW_SERVICE_MARKER -u OPENCLAW_SERVICE_VERSION -u OPENCLAW_SERVICE_MANAGED_ENV_KEYS -u OPENCLAW_GATEWAY_SERVICE_PID -u OPENCLAW_LAUNCHD_LABEL -u OPENCLAW_SYSTEMD_UNIT -u OPENCLAW_WINDOWS_TASK_NAME -u OPENCLAW_WRAPPER PATH=/Users/jason/.nvm/versions/node/v24.14.0/bin:$PATH OPENCLAW_VITEST_MAX_WORKERS=2 OPENCLAW_VITEST_FS_MODULE_CACHE_PATH=/tmp/openclaw-pr-91586-vitest-fix2-20260613T0005 node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/infra/update-runner.test.ts src/cli/update-cli.test.ts src/infra/package-update-steps.test.ts src/commands/doctor/shared/release-configured-plugin-installs.test.ts src/flows/doctor-health-contributions.test.ts src/gateway/server-methods/update.test.ts\ngit diff --check upstream/main...HEAD\ngit merge-tree --write-tree upstream/main HEAD\n.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode branch --base upstream/main --codex-bin /Users/jason/.codex/openclaw-pr-autopilot/bin/codex-persist-sessions --model codex=kepler-alpha --thinking codex=high\n```\n\nEvidence after fix: The focused suite passed 291 tests across five Vitest shards, including the CLI advisory continuation path, shared advisory classifier, configured-plugin doctor flow, generic update runner, and gateway error/no-restart contract. `git diff --check` was clean. The current-main merge simulation was conflict-free and produced tree 42874f22bd78022574677a46e82eedca289c354b. Fresh persisted branch Kepler autoreview reported no accepted/actionable findings and judged the patch correct.\n\nCopied live output excerpt from the real packed-package updater run on ancestor 377924d03129cc97b094c1d2681148e37487e5f0:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"status\": \"ok\",\n  \"mode\": \"npm\",\n  \"doctor\": {\n    \"name\": \"openclaw doctor\",\n    \"exitCode\": 86,\n    \"advisory\": { \"kind\": \"package-post-install-doctor\" },\n    \"stderrTail\": \"Skipped package-manager repair for configured plugin discord during package update; rerun openclaw doctor --fix after the update completes.\"\n  },\n  \"postUpdatePluginsStatus\": \"warning\"\n}\n```\n\nObserved result after fix: The typed advisory gate authorizes only the intended recoverable doctor result in the CLI package updater, which continues into guaranteed post-core plugin convergence. Unknown exits, missing or malformed results, killed runs, signals, and timeouts remain blocking. The generic update runner's advisory/deferral additions and their tests were removed, restoring its existing blocking doctor contract instead of allowing it to report success without convergence.\n\nWhat was not tested: Current head did not rerun the packed-package real update, a managed gateway restart, production/test type checks, or a broad Testbox lane. The prior real package success proof remains attributable to ancestor 377924d03129cc97b094c1d2681148e37487e5f0. No Crabbox or Mantis lane was run, and no live or protected channel was touched.\n",
